title: Young moose sighted near Highway 16 and Boychuk Drive in Saskatoon
content: Saskatoon police said on Saturday afternoon they received a report of a young moose in the area of Highway 16 and Boychuk Drive.  Motorists in the area are asked to drive with extra caution, police said.  Officers have not yet found the moose.  [video-player videoid="z2nn4bO7hGc" /]  This follows a moose spotting on 17th Street West near the Meewasin trails on Friday morning. Police received several calls about the moose, and an officer witnessed the moose leaving the area.  During the last several weeks, city police have responded to other calls involving moose roaming the city this spring.  The first was on April 20, when two moose were spotted in a city park. On May 9, two more were captured in the city’s north end.  [video-player videoid="9abiZ5SK55o" /]
